nib.text:
A rideshare driver was hospitalized after a shooting in Eastview Thursday evening, officials said. 

At around 5:45 p.m., police responded to a report of a hit-and-run crash near the corner of Old Hudson Road and White Bear Avenue. 

Upon arrival, officers found a man who had been shot. 

Medics transported the victim to an area hospital where he was listed in critical condition. He is expected to survive, however, according to a report from [FOX9.](https://www.fox9.com/news/rideshare-driver-in-critical-condition-after-being-shot-carjacked-in-st-paul)

The driver reportedly told police that he had picked up one or more rideshare passengers who then shot him and drove away in his SUV. 

Detectives are investigating. 

No arrests were reported.
